 <title>Maze without limits with straws and clothespins</title>
 <link>http://escornabot.com/web/en/2015-03-09/maze-without-limits-straws-and-clothespins</link>
 <description>&lt;a href=&quot;/web/en/2015-03-09/maze-without-limits-straws-and-clothespins&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;teaserimage&quot; typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;http://escornabot.com/web/sites/default/files/styles/teaser_image/public/node_attachs/clothespin_straw.jpg?itok=JCTphR46&quot; alt=&quot;Maze without limits with straws and clothespins&quot; title=&quot;Maze without limits with straws and clothespins&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://plus.google.com/116520498030072719107/&quot;&gt;Jorge Lobo&lt;/a&gt;, teacher at &lt;em&gt;CEIP Lope de Vega&lt;/em&gt; school in Madrid, proposes an interesting way of building &lt;strong&gt;mazes with barriers made of straws and clothespins&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The maze challenge consists in programming the Escornabot in order to cross the maze and don&#039;t crash with the walls. One error will cause the building destruction by the bug. Fortunatly, these barriers are recyclable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

